[SN]TITLE[SN]
Lost WW1 Manchester Piccadilly memorial replaced 50 years on

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A new memorial to honour 87 railwaymen killed in World War One has been unveiled at Manchester Piccadilly train station, replacing the original which went missing 50 years ago.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
5 May 2016 Last updated at 07:16 BST
The tribute to workers from London Road goods depot was lost during a station redevelopment.
BBC North West Tonight's Stuart Flinders reports.
